# Theme Token Colors Only

- Never use hardcoded colors in app code (`#hex`, `rgb()`, `hsl()`, inline style colors).
- Never use raw Tailwind palette color utilities for product UI surfaces/text (e.g. `bg-zinc-900`, `text-amber-300`) unless explicitly approved for one-off visualizations.
- Always use **shadcn semantic token classes** from `app/globals.css` (e.g. `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `bg-primary`, `border-border`, `bg-accent`, `text-muted-foreground`).
- Dark surfaces use inversion: `bg-foreground text-background` — not custom tokens.
- If a needed color does not exist, retune an existing shadcn variable in `:root` / `.dark` before adding a new one. Expose in `@theme inline` only when necessary.
- Keep naming semantic and reusable (`accent`, `muted`), not context-specific (`dashboard-card-bg`).

## Example

```tsx
// ❌ Avoid
<div className="bg-[#f1eadf] text-[#171717] border-[#e2d6c2]" />
<div className="bg-cream-surface text-ink-warm border-cream-border" />

// ✅ Use tokens
<div className="bg-card text-foreground border-border" />
<div className="bg-foreground text-background" />
```
